        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 1:14PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 114 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Gardner to near Otis to Elmer. Movement
was northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alexandria, Boyce, Alexandria International Airport, Gardner, Otis,
Elmer, Calcasieu, and Woodworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
